{
  "texts": [
    "Concod outperformed four existing deletion detection tools (Pindel, SVseq2, Break-Dancer, and DELLY) in sensitivity and precision (Cai et al. 2017).",
    "However, this tool was limited to identifying only short structural variations in the sequences.",
    "Then a visualization-based ML model, DeepSV, was developed (Cai et al. 2019).",
    "DeepSV is based on deep learning and is used for identifying long deletions within the genomic sequence.",
    "The tool is optimized to work with noisy training data."
  ]
}